FunboxRookie

Target IP: 192.168.194.107

Scanning



There are three TCP ports open on the target machine. As usual, I will start my enumeration with port 80.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

Doing a directory search indicates there is robots.txt.

The content of robots.txt is shown above. Apparently /logs/ is disallowed.

Port 21: FTP

Since anonymous login is allowed, I used mget * to download all files. There are two more hidden files called .@admins and .@users which I had to download manually.


I saved all these files on my local machine.


The .@admins contains a base64 string. After decoding it, we get the message above. This message informs us the zip files contain the SSH key of that user. Maybe we can use john to crack the passwords?


Trying to crack the password of zip file only worked for tom.zip. Using zip2john to crack tom.zip, I obtained the password iubire. I used this password to obtain the SSH key of tom. I changed the permission of the key to 400 and logged in as the user tom using the SSH key.

Exploitation


Now I have a foothold on the machine as tom. It loks like rbash is in the way so we cannot use commands like cd. To overcome this, I used the following command to gain a non-restricted shell ssh tom@192.168.194.107 -i id_rsa bash --noprofile.

Privilege Escalation


Inside tom's home directory, there is an interesting file called .mysql_history. It contains the password xx11yy22!.


Looks like Tom can run all commands. Entering su -i gives us a root shell.

Flags


The local.txt is located inside the same location where we land our shell as tom.


The proof.txt flag once I leveraged the privileges from tom to root.
